place.name: LITTLE WITCHINGHAM
place.gazetteerText: WITCHINGHAM (Little), a parish in St. Faith district, Norfolk; 8½ miles E by S of Elmham r. station. Post town, Great Witchingham, under Norwich. Acres, 738. Real property, £1,342. Pop., 33. Houses, 7. The living is a rectory, annexed to Great W. The church is old and plain. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
